<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/UNICEF-107x107.png?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Pneumonia, world’s leading infectious child killer — UNICEF" class="amp-wp-295b586"> Kills 2,000 children daily globally  UNICEF says pneumonia is the world’s leading infectious killer of children, claiming the lives of more than 2,000 under the age of five every day. Dr. Sanjana Bhardwaj, the Chief of Health, UNICEF Nigeria made this known at the commemoration of the 2019 World Pneumonia Day and World Prematurity Day. The event was organised by “Save the Children’’, a Non-Governmental Organisation (NGO) in collaboration with UNICEF and other supporters in Abuja on Monday. Continue reading Pneumonia, world’s leading infectious child killer — UNICEF at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard